&nbsp;
The replica of Russia did not make itself wait with the Kremlin who rejected the accusations of the United States. "We saw the news about it. As always, such accusations seem completely unfounded and undemonstrated", commented the spokesman of the Russian Presidency, Dmitri Peskov.
&nbsp;
Meanwhile the US Treasury Department has announced sanctions against 300 companies in Russia, China and other countries accused of providing weapons or components useful to the Moscow war effort. According to the United States National Institutes of Health, chloropicrine is used both as a weapon and as a pesticide. If inhaled, the substance represents a health risk. Russia claims to no longer possess a chemical arsenal. &nbsp;&nbsp;
<h2> The last from the front
A Russian missile attack has caused the wounding of at least thirteen people in Odessa, the harbour resort in the South-West of Ukraine. He reported on Telegram the mayor of the city, Gennadyi Trukhanov, explaining that "civil infrastructures were destroyed" and "13 people were injured". Trukhanov added that firefighters are fighting "a fire" of large size, without providing further details. Oleg Kiper, governor of the Odessa region, gave a budget of 14 wounded.

